WEBVTT

00:06.750 --> 00:09.071
[wind howling]

00:16.040 --> 00:17.746
[First Mate Xander]
Shine those lights!

00:17.750 --> 00:19.240
-Let's go! Lock it down!
-[Ca|vin] I got it!

00:19.250 --> 00:20.740
Watch out! Brace!
It's a big one!

00:24.420 --> 00:25.876
[Xander]
Man! Oh, no!

00:25.880 --> 00:27.416
We're getting
hammered out here!

00:27.420 --> 00:28.910
Everything up!

00:28.920 --> 00:31.320
Nets coming up!

00:31.330 --> 00:33.616
-[Xander] Bring it in!
-[Chris] Steady!

00:33.620 --> 00:34.746
[Xander] Pull!

00:37.250 --> 00:40.458
[ominous music playing]

00:40.460 --> 00:43.076
-[Calvin] What the hell?
-[Chris] Is there somethin'
in there?

00:46.080 --> 00:48.958
[Chris] It's big!
It-- It's moving!

00:48.960 --> 00:51.076
[men shouting]

00:51.080 --> 00:52.707
-[Xander] Chris!
-[Chris] No! It's right there!

00:52.710 --> 00:55.611
[indistinct shouting]

00:55.620 --> 00:57.451
Chris! Let's take 'em out!

00:59.330 --> 01:01.207
Shark?

01:01.210 --> 01:03.166
That ain't no shark!

01:03.170 --> 01:05.161
Xander? You see it?
It's over there!

01:08.000 --> 01:10.116
Come on, come on,
where are you at?

01:10.120 --> 01:11.200
Show yourself.

01:14.040 --> 01:15.371
Oh! Chris! Watch out!

01:15.380 --> 01:17.166
-[screams]
-Comin' around!

01:17.170 --> 01:19.377
Goin' your way, Cal!
Calvin, head it off!

01:19.380 --> 01:21.029
In the hold!
Get it down there!

01:21.040 --> 01:23.201
-Get it down there!
-[creature shrieks]

01:23.210 --> 01:25.326
What the hell is it?

01:25.330 --> 01:27.378
-Oh, Xander!
-[Xander] Chris.

01:27.380 --> 01:29.996
-God, Xander!
-Chris!

01:30.000 --> 01:32.070
Oh, God!

01:32.080 --> 01:33.877
[groaning]

01:35.000 --> 01:36.661
Come on!

01:36.670 --> 01:38.376
He's lost
a lot of blood, but...

01:38.380 --> 01:40.701
Tamp it down.
Get in there good and tight.

01:40.710 --> 01:42.917
[groaning]

01:42.920 --> 01:46.708
This is the North Star,
vessel number 53422N.

01:46.710 --> 01:49.702
I_ have a crew member
In_need of Immediate
medical evacuation. Over.

01:49.710 --> 01:51.746
-[dispatcher]
Nature of injury?
-Bite to the abdomen,

01:51.750 --> 01:53.615
severe blood loss. Over.

01:53.620 --> 01:54.780
[dispatcher]
What bit him?

01:54.790 --> 01:56.701
1--

01:56.710 --> 01:59.110
I got no idea.

02:00.920 --> 02:03.206
[thunder]

02:05.210 --> 02:08.168
[loud pounding]

02:09.580 --> 02:12.617
[pounding continuing]

02:17.290 --> 02:19.201
[soft high-pitched calling]

02:20.830 --> 02:24.459
[woman's ethereal
singing echoing]

02:31.710 --> 02:33.325
[Xander] What is it?

02:34.380 --> 02:39.329
[singing grows louder]

02:57.620 --> 02:59.952
[helicopter approaching]

03:04.460 --> 03:05.916
[SEAL] Secure.

03:07.620 --> 03:10.453
Let's see what you
caught tonight, Captain.

03:10.460 --> 03:13.327
What I caught is none
of your business!

03:13.330 --> 03:15.036
You're just here
for my injured crewman.

03:15.040 --> 03:16.610
Of course.

03:16.620 --> 03:17.951
We'll be needing him
as well.

03:19.830 --> 03:21.240
[SEAL] Let's go!

03:21.250 --> 03:23.206
-[radio chatter]
-[winch whirring]

03:25.500 --> 03:27.491
Now then, Captain...

03:27.500 --> 03:29.240
I'm entitled
to that catch!

03:30.830 --> 03:35.199
[creature breathing]

03:40.670 --> 03:42.376
-[dart fires]
-[creature shrieks]

03:45.500 --> 03:46.615
Let's go!

04:05.420 --> 04:08.412
[placid high-pitched calls]

04:11.960 --> 04:15.168
[woman vocalizing]

04:23.960 --> 04:26.747
[guitars playing sea chantey]

04:29.920 --> 04:32.115
[college girl]
Look what we found!

04:32.120 --> 04:34.532
Margaritas!

04:34.540 --> 04:36.997
Whoo!

04:37.000 --> 04:39.616
[girl] Do you want
a pretzel?!

04:39.620 --> 04:40.700
[bell rings]

04:42.040 --> 04:43.951
[crowd cheering]

04:43.960 --> 04:46.952
It was more
than 150 years ago

04:46.960 --> 04:48.996
when a local fishing captain,

04:49.000 --> 04:52.379
Charles H. Pownall,
fell in love with a mermaid

04:52.380 --> 04:53.995
in these very waters,

04:54.000 --> 04:56.958
enchanted by
her beautiful Siren song.

04:56.960 --> 04:58.416
I love you, fisherman.

04:58.420 --> 04:59.990
I love you, mermaid.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.286
But one day,
he went to the bay,

05:02.290 --> 05:04.531
and his mermaid was gone

05:04.540 --> 05:06.417
back to her home
In the sea,

05:06.420 --> 05:08.035
never to return.

05:08.040 --> 05:11.168
And that is how,
thanks to Charles H. Pownall,

05:11.170 --> 05:14.412
Bristol Cove became
the Mermaid Capital
of the World.

05:14.420 --> 05:17.116
[confetti cannons popping]

05:22.170 --> 05:24.377
Wow. Thank you.

05:24.380 --> 05:28.999
That was my great-great-great-
grandfather depicted there,

05:29.000 --> 05:32.413
so as you can see,
our family goes back
a long ways in Bristol Cove.

05:32.420 --> 05:35.617
Now please allow me to introduce
my beautiful wife Elaine

05:35.620 --> 05:37.872
and our two wonderful sons,
Doug and Ben.

05:37.880 --> 05:40.667
[applause]

05:40.670 --> 05:42.820
It seems, uh,

05:42.830 --> 05:44.878
Ben may have been caught up
in the parade traffic,

05:44.880 --> 05:47.667
but I can assure you
he is here in spirit.

05:47.670 --> 05:50.616
So to all the good people
of Bristol Cove,

05:50.620 --> 05:53.783
it is our great honor
to bestow this monument

05:53.790 --> 05:56.452
to one of our town's
founding fathers,

05:56.460 --> 05:59.452
Charles H. Pownall.

05:59.460 --> 06:01.246
[applause]

06:01.250 --> 06:05.493
[sea chantey playing]

06:05.500 --> 06:07.821
-Where the hell's _Be_n? Hmm?
-[camera clicking]

06:09.040 --> 06:11.873
Now I don't know

06:11.880 --> 06:14.326
What tomorrow brings

06:14.330 --> 06:17.288
But I know one day

06:17.290 --> 06:19.952
I'll get what I need

06:25.580 --> 06:28.117
Hola! How'd it go?

06:28.120 --> 06:30.076
Rescued a Steller.

06:30.080 --> 06:31.456
She's in pretty bad shape.

06:31.460 --> 06:33.246
She's tagged.
She's one of ours.

06:33.250 --> 06:34.239
Where'd you find her?

06:34.250 --> 06:35.490
Out by Scott's Point.

06:35.500 --> 06:36.615
That's pretty far.

06:36.620 --> 06:38.030
Yeah, about 30 miles

06:38.040 --> 06:39.450
outside her usual range.

06:39.460 --> 06:41.166
Probably looking for food.

06:41.170 --> 06:43.240
[sea lion bellowing]

06:43.250 --> 06:44.740
Don't worry, girl.

06:44.750 --> 06:46.661
We're gonna take
good care of you.

06:46.670 --> 06:48.160
[high-pitched groans]

06:48.170 --> 06:50.240
Come on.

06:53.670 --> 06:54.955
She's starving out there.

06:54.960 --> 06:56.496
It's a good thing
we went out today.

06:56.500 --> 06:58.491
Not sure your dad
would agree with that.

06:58.500 --> 07:00.912
Well, I'll add that
to the list of things
we don't agree on.

07:00.920 --> 07:02.535
Like you and me
being together?

07:02.540 --> 07:07.534
Hey. Look, if I did
everything my dad told me,

07:07.540 --> 07:09.496
well, I'd be my brother.

07:10.620 --> 07:11.780
You want to come
over later?

07:11.790 --> 07:13.872
I promised my dad
I'd make him dinner.

07:13.880 --> 07:15.871
Third time this week?

07:15.880 --> 07:17.495
Luclq guy.

07:17.500 --> 07:19.206
He needs me.

07:19.210 --> 07:20.529
He'd be at the drive-thru
every night if I didn't cook.

07:20.540 --> 07:22.576
Seriously, it's disturbing.

07:22.580 --> 07:25.413
I could come by after
for dessert.

07:25.420 --> 07:26.910
Spend the night?

07:26.920 --> 07:28.456
If you want me to.

07:28.460 --> 07:29.996
What do you think?

07:32.790 --> 07:34.997
[music playing in bar]

07:39.710 --> 07:42.531
Hey, man.
Thought you guys were
out past Bowers Ridge.

07:42.540 --> 07:44.110
You're back early.

07:44.120 --> 07:47.499
Yeah. I need to talk to you
about something.

07:47.500 --> 07:48.535
All right.

07:48.540 --> 07:49.780
Boys.

07:51.920 --> 07:54.741
We said keep
this between us.
Don't tell anybody.

07:54.750 --> 07:56.661
Ben knows about this stuff,
all right?

07:56.670 --> 07:58.069
He can help us.

07:58.080 --> 07:59.536
He's one of us.

07:59.540 --> 08:00.780
He wasn't
on the boat with us.

08:00.790 --> 08:02.451
He doesn't fish
With us no more.

08:08.210 --> 08:10.280
We caught somethin'
out there.

08:10.290 --> 08:11.700
I mean,
it's just somethin' we...

08:11.710 --> 08:13.826
we ain't never seen before.

08:13.830 --> 08:15.616
It attacked Chris.

08:15.620 --> 08:17.497
He had
to get airlifted out,

08:17.500 --> 08:19.491
big-ass military
commando helicopter.

08:19.500 --> 08:21.661
Navy SEALs,
the whole deal.

08:21.670 --> 08:24.457
CG says they have
no record of the evac,

08:24.460 --> 08:26.701
like it never happened.

08:26.710 --> 08:27.574
He's just gone.

08:27.580 --> 08:30.071
What do you mean
he's gone?

08:30.080 --> 08:31.661
You really don't know
what attacked him?

08:31.670 --> 08:33.740
[Sean clears throat]

08:40.290 --> 08:41.951
A mermaid?

08:41.960 --> 08:43.666
It didn't
look like that, okay?

08:43.670 --> 08:46.958
This...
this was a predator.

08:49.420 --> 08:51.786
Okay, that was a good one.

08:51.790 --> 08:53.781
Yeah, very, very well done.

08:53.790 --> 08:55.030
You almost had me there.

08:55.040 --> 08:56.996
Dude, this is real.

08:57.000 --> 08:59.787
Hey, why else would they
take it from us, huh?

08:59.790 --> 09:01.576
Wait.

09:03.580 --> 09:05.036
Here. Look.

09:05.040 --> 09:06.951
Okay.

09:11.790 --> 09:14.076
Xander, man,
this could be anything.

09:15.420 --> 09:18.241
I don't know
what you call it,

09:18.250 --> 09:22.459
but, trust me, it's not
what you think it is.

09:33.880 --> 09:35.871
[Decker] We had a report
six weeks ago.

09:35.880 --> 09:37.700
Japanese fishermen claimed
they saw a sea creature

09:37.710 --> 09:39.109
off the Kuril Islands.

09:39.120 --> 09:41.281
Then some carcasses
washed ashore in Alaska

09:41.290 --> 09:43.372
with strange bite marks
all over them.

09:43.380 --> 09:45.530
Then five days ago,
our research vessel

09:45.540 --> 09:48.452
picked up unidentified
frequencies coming
from the Bering Strait.

09:48.460 --> 09:50.325
We knew something
was out there.

09:50.330 --> 09:51.661
That's when I alerted
your people.

09:51.670 --> 09:54.241
And you're sure this is
what you think it is?

09:54.250 --> 09:56.115
Well, Admiral...

09:56.120 --> 09:58.668
-[door opens]
-...why don't you
judge for yourself?

10:10.880 --> 10:16.159
[Siren song echoing]

10:21.120 --> 10:22.917
[knock on door]

10:24.670 --> 10:25.785
[Elaine]
Good morning, clear.

10:27.080 --> 10:30.868
Your father is
terribly angry with you.

10:30.880 --> 10:33.030
Good morning to you, too.

10:33.040 --> 10:35.611
Anthony?

10:35.620 --> 10:38.248
I don't give a rat's ass
if your father's angry.

10:38.250 --> 10:40.878
A lot of things
make him angry,

10:40.880 --> 10:42.416
like the fact that a woman
who can't walk

10:42.420 --> 10:45.207
insists
on buying $600 shoes.

10:45.210 --> 10:47.747
-You know what he called
me the other day?
-What?

10:47.750 --> 10:49.377
Bitch on wheels.

10:49.380 --> 10:51.951
That's actually pretty funny.

10:51.960 --> 10:54.246
I thought so, too.

10:54.250 --> 10:56.616
Do you know why it was okay?

10:56.620 --> 10:59.874
Because it was
behind closed doors.

10:59.880 --> 11:01.871
Family rule--

11:01.880 --> 11:04.326
you can say whatever the hell
awful thing you want in private,

11:04.330 --> 11:05.536
but in public...

11:07.080 --> 11:10.538
This is a face that keeps
Mommy in nice shoes.

11:10.540 --> 11:12.280
I get it.

11:12.290 --> 11:14.076
No, I don't think you do.

11:14.080 --> 11:17.072
Because if you did,
you'd show up.

11:20.380 --> 11:22.746
and you wouldn't leave
your father up on stage

11:22.750 --> 11:24.570
with his pants
around his ankles.

11:24.580 --> 11:26.411
You know what, Mom?

11:26.420 --> 11:29.537
If you guys want
to put a show on
for the whole town,

11:29.540 --> 11:31.701
that's your business,
but I...

11:31.710 --> 11:33.109
I don't want anything
to do with it.

11:33.120 --> 11:35.372
I got other things
to worry about.

11:36.750 --> 11:38.911
The spawning habits
of a bunch of plankton

11:38.920 --> 11:40.160
are more important
than family.

11:40.170 --> 11:41.876
That's not what I'm saying.

11:41.880 --> 11:45.953
And I really
_don't want to have_
this conversation again.

11:45.960 --> 11:48.781
Ben, I need this family
to keep working.

11:50.960 --> 11:53.702
And I'm not willing
to suffer for nothing.

11:56.830 --> 11:58.206
Okay, I hear you.

11:59.960 --> 12:03.111
Doug tells me that
you're hot and heavy
with Maddie Bishop.

12:03.120 --> 12:06.112
Yeah, we're dating.

12:06.120 --> 12:08.247
You always had a thing
for the wild girls.

12:08.250 --> 12:10.241
I gotta get
some stuff done.

12:10.250 --> 12:13.162
[door closes]

12:16.620 --> 12:19.453
Always had a thing
for the wild girls, huh?

12:19.460 --> 12:21.246
I'm sorry.

12:21.250 --> 12:22.820
She didn't know
you were in here.

12:22.830 --> 12:24.616
So if it weren't
for your brother,

12:24.620 --> 12:26.997
she wouldn't even know
we were seeing each other?

12:27.000 --> 12:28.991
Believe me,
with my family,

12:29.000 --> 12:31.912
nothing good
ever comes from sharing.

12:31.920 --> 12:35.378
You never know.
Your mom and I might
actually hit it off.

12:35.380 --> 12:37.666
Yeah, you might be right.

12:37.670 --> 12:41.037
I mean, you're
exactly the kind of girl
she'd want me to be with.

12:41.040 --> 12:43.326
Oh, yeah?
What kind of girl is that?

12:43.330 --> 12:45.036
Beautiful.

12:47.670 --> 12:48.739
Smart.

12:51.040 --> 12:52.200
Funny.

12:55.250 --> 12:56.410
Passionate.

12:56.420 --> 12:58.206
[chuckles]

12:58.210 --> 13:00.451
And that smile

13:00.460 --> 13:03.952
that could power
a small city.

13:03.960 --> 13:05.871
Ah, yes.

13:05.880 --> 13:08.451
Ah, that famous
Pownall charm.

13:17.460 --> 13:19.826
[rock music playing]

13:21.960 --> 13:24.076
Mm! No, dude, Aberdeen.

13:24.080 --> 13:26.958
The best weed is in Aberdeen.

13:26.960 --> 13:30.077
[laughs]
Seriously gourmet Kush.

13:30.080 --> 13:31.820
[laughter]

13:31.830 --> 13:33.457
[Jerry]
Even my mom likes it.

13:33.460 --> 13:36.247
I don't remember him being
such a burner in high school.

13:36.250 --> 13:38.457
Yeah, that was
more your crowd, right?

13:38.460 --> 13:40.280
Oh, all right, golden boy.

13:48.420 --> 13:50.741
Hey, I'll be back
in a minute.

13:50.750 --> 13:51.819
Okay.

13:58.540 --> 14:01.031
I swear I'm gonna kill you
if you go out too far!

14:06.960 --> 14:08.029
[Ben] Hey.

14:08.040 --> 14:10.577
You okay?

14:10.580 --> 14:13.492
You're not seriously pissed
at me, are you?

14:13.500 --> 14:14.910
I shouldn't have told you.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.535
Should have known better.

14:16.540 --> 14:17.996
Think about what
you're asking me to believe.

14:18.000 --> 14:19.740
I get it.
You don't come out

14:19.750 --> 14:21.160
_ on the boat
With us anymore.

14:21.170 --> 14:22.159
You weren't there.

14:22.170 --> 14:25.207
They took Chris.

14:25.210 --> 14:27.166
They don't want people
to know about this.

14:27.170 --> 14:30.037
Look, I don't know
what happened to Chris.

14:30.040 --> 14:32.531
Maybe he's
in a military hospital.

14:32.540 --> 14:34.610
We're gonna find him, Xan.

14:34.620 --> 14:37.032
This isn't part
of some huge cover-up,

14:37.040 --> 14:39.110
and it's not_ because
of some mythical creature

14:39.120 --> 14:40.326
that you guys think
that you caught.

14:40.330 --> 14:41.991
So you're telling me
you know everything

14:42.000 --> 14:43.956
-there is to know about--
-No, of course not!

14:43.960 --> 14:45.496
Then look me in the eye
and you tell me

14:45.500 --> 14:47.320
that maybe-- maybe there
is something down there

14:47.330 --> 14:48.706
that we haven't
seen before.

14:53.790 --> 14:56.281
-Xan. ..
-Just--

14:56.290 --> 14:58.497
Just do it.

14:58.500 --> 15:00.570
Okay.

15:00.580 --> 15:02.536
Sure.

15:02.540 --> 15:04.667
95% _of the oceans
remain unexplored.

15:04.670 --> 15:07.377
So it could happen?

15:07.380 --> 15:09.450
[ominous music playing]

15:12.000 --> 15:13.240
Xander, man, I love you.

15:13.250 --> 15:14.660
You know that.

15:14.670 --> 15:16.991
But as a friend,
I'm telling you,

15:17.000 --> 15:19.616
you gotta stop
talking like this.

15:19.620 --> 15:22.248
What would it take?

15:22.250 --> 15:24.878
Hmm?

15:24.880 --> 15:26.199
For you to believe me?

15:27.210 --> 15:28.871
I'd have to see one.

15:34.330 --> 15:35.570
That's it.

15:38.040 --> 15:39.496
That's exactly right.

15:41.080 --> 15:42.661
We gotta catch another one.

15:44.790 --> 15:46.371
[girl]
Lucas, get back here!

15:48.380 --> 15:49.495
[loud splash]

16:06.710 --> 16:08.075
[screams]

16:08.080 --> 16:10.878
Shark! Shark! Shark!

16:10.880 --> 16:13.166
Aah! Aah!

16:13.170 --> 16:14.455
Shark!

16:20.210 --> 16:21.199
What are you thinking?

16:25.330 --> 16:27.912
[girl]
I can't even believe it.

16:27.920 --> 16:30.411
It's disgusting.

16:30.420 --> 16:34.288
This damage definitely
wasn't inflicted
by an orca.

16:34.290 --> 16:37.077
_The bite radius
is way too small.

16:37.080 --> 16:38.911
So what then?

16:38.920 --> 16:41.241
Well,
it's not another shark.

16:41.250 --> 16:43.161
_ _There are _
a million explanations.

16:43.170 --> 16:44.239
Okay?

16:44.250 --> 16:45.740
Caught in a boat prop,

16:45.750 --> 16:47.991
sea lion bit the carcass?

16:50.080 --> 16:53.243
What if there's
a new predator out there?

16:53.250 --> 16:55.070
One that we haven't
seen before?

16:55.080 --> 16:59.198
That can rip the head
clean off a mako shark?

16:59.210 --> 17:03.453
Then I might have to cancel
my scuba trip next weekend.

17:03.460 --> 17:06.827
[music playing]

17:06.830 --> 17:11.824
Always walkin'
a vicious circle

17:14.380 --> 17:16.371
[volume increases]
Oh, me

17:19.040 --> 17:21.076
[tires screech]

17:28.330 --> 17:29.285
Hey!

17:29.290 --> 17:30.746
Are you okay?

17:34.290 --> 17:35.450
Do you need help?

17:52.960 --> 17:54.996
[male doctor, on phone]
Is she having
trouble breathing?

17:55.000 --> 17:57.321
No, no, no,
her breathing's fine.

17:57.330 --> 17:59.207
Uh, a little heaw.

17:59.210 --> 18:00.325
[doctor]
Okay, I'll head out now.

18:00.330 --> 18:01.319
[Ben]
Are you sure?

18:01.330 --> 18:02.570
I mean, I'm happy
to drive her

18:02.580 --> 18:04.707
down to the hospital
